            "body": "I'm not really talking about when I'm developing code, I'm more considering the workflow when reviewing other peoples code.\r\n\r\nI use https://github.com/harrisoncramer/gitlab.nvim to code review PRs, this in turn makes use of https://github.com/sindrets/diffview.nvim to display the diff, which uses nvim's diff view. Sometimes this makes it hard to spot small changes as word diffs aren't present. So I open lazygit either in another terminal window or using a neovim plugin. I'd prefer to stay inside neovim as I have access to the LSPs and diagnostics in the diff and I can more seamlessly navigate the code from a diff.",
